cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper deals with zero-shot recognition in image processing, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves machine learning techniques for adapting the semantic feature space, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the domain shift and hubness problems, which are common issues in machine learning and can be categorized under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for semantic feature space, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves experiments with image datasets, which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
